India sets 21-day 'complete lockdown' to stop coronavirus spread It could be the biggest lockdown of its kind in human history.
Addressing the nation in a televised address, Modi said the strict lockdown was necessary to "save India and every Indian."
FILE PHOTO: India's Prime Minister Narendra Modi in New Delhi on Feb. 25, 2020.
Prime Minister Modi also pledged a budget of $2 billion to be used to help treat the pandemic.
Police patrol a street during a government-imposed lockdown as a preventive measure against the COVID-19 coronavirus, in Amritsar, India, March 24, 2020.